tafsir[10]{c,v,t}:
  53,1,"He (may He be glorified) swore by the star when it descends."
  53,3,"And he did not speak this Qur’ān out of following his desires."
  53,4,"This Qur’ān is nothing but a revelation which Allah revealed to him through the medium of Gabriel (peace be upon him)"
  53,7,"Whilst he was on the highest horizon."
  53,9,"So his closeness to him was the distance of two bow lengths or even closer."
  53,11,"The heart of Muhammad (peace be upon him) did not lie about what his eye saw."
  53,13,"And Muhammad (peace be upon him) had seen Gabriel (peace be upon him) in his true form another time on the night he was taken for the journey."
  53,15,"By this tree is the Garden of Refuge."
  53,16,"When the lote tree was covered through the command of Allah by something great whose true nature only Allah knows."
  53,22,"This distribution which you made with your desires is an unjust distribution."